(tracks 7, 13)}}\n* [[Greg Phillinganes]] \u2013 keyboards {{small|(track 11)}}\n* [[Tim Pierce]] \u2013 heavy metal guitar {{small|(track 8)}}\n* [[Jeff Porcaro]] \u2013 drums {{small|(track 7)}}\n* [[Steve Porcaro]] \u2013 synthesizer {{small|(tracks 7, 13)}}, keyboards and programming {{small|(9)}}\n* [[Teddy Riley]] \u2013 producer, engineer, mixing, and synthesizers {{small|(tracks 1\u20136, 14)}}; keyboards {{small|(1\u20136)}}; guitar {{small|(1, 2)}}; rhythm arrangements {{small|(2\u20136, 14)}}; synthesizer arrangements {{small|(3\u20136, 14)}}; drums and arrangements {{small|(1)}}\n* [[Thom Russo]] \u2013 engineer {{small|(track 14)}}\n* [[Slash (musician)|Slash]] \u2013 special guitar performance {{small|(track 8 intro, track 10)}}\n* [[Bruce Swedien]] \u2013 producer {{small|(tracks 1)}}, co-producer {{small|(tracks 7, 11\u201313)}}, engineer and mixing {{small|(1\u20137, 11\u201314)}}, arrangements and keyboards {{small|(1)}}, drums {{small|(1, 11, 12)}}, percussion {{small|(11, 12)}}\n* Jai Winding \u2013 keyboards and programming {{small|(track 9)}}, piano and bass guitar {{small|(12)}}\n* Mystery Girl {{small|([[Princess St\u00e9phanie of Monaco]])}} \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 3)}}\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Charts ==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n=== Weekly charts ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (1991\u20132010)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|1|artist=Michael Jackson|album=Dangerous|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 27, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Pro-M\u00fasica Brasil|Brazilian Top 10 CD BPD]]<ref name=\"abpdI\">{{cite web|author=ds |url=http://www.abpd.org.br/noticias_internas.asp?noticia=173 |title=Charts July 6 \u2013 July 12, 2009 |publisher=ABPD |accessdate=January 10, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090922030723/http://www.abpd.org.br/noticias_internas.asp?noticia=173|archivedate=September 22, 2009}}</ref>\n| 4\n|-\n!